	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>rainwarrior</b> [ Sat Mar 08, 2014 9:59 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Can you stretch scanlines horizontaly?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If you can make a pattern that repeats vertically (e.g. a checkerboard), you could build a single nametable that has one row of the pattern at each of several stretched widths. This would let you use a repeated vertical split scroll to tile the pattern over all or part of the screen without having to dedicate the entire nametable, allowing you to progressively &quot;stretch&quot; the pattern just by adjusting the vertical srcoll position used during vertical tiling, without having to upload any new nametable data between frames.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


